entities.PortalRenderHelper/RelativeTeleportTrigger.placements.name.default=Relative Teleport Trigger
entities.PortalRenderHelper/RelativeTeleportTrigger.placements.description.default=Trigger that teleports the player by a offset as defined by the trigger's node.

entities.PortalRenderHelper/RelativeTeleportTrigger.attributes.description.flag=Optional flag that can enable / disable the trigger. Trigger is always active if left blank.
entities.PortalRenderHelper/RelativeTeleportTrigger.attributes.description.invert=Invert how the flag is used. Off = Flag must be enabled for trigger to be enabled, On = Flag must be disabled for trigger to be enabled.
entities.PortalRenderHelper/RelativeTeleportTrigger.attributes.description.angle=The angle in degrees going out relative to the angle going in, where positive is clockwise.
entities.PortalRenderHelper/RelativeTeleportTrigger.attributes.description.changeTargetAngle=Whether the target angle of the camera should also be changed. With this disabled, the camera will smoothly rotate back to its original orientation after traveling through the portal.


entities.PortalRenderHelper/PortalRenderPoly.placements.name.default=Portal Render Polygon
entities.PortalRenderHelper/PortalRenderPoly.placements.description.default=Defines the edges of the portal renderer. The actual rendering is done in a foreground styleground, which must also be added to the map.

entities.PortalRenderHelper/PortalRenderPoly.attributes.description.closed=Whether the polygon is closed. On = Only the region defined by the polygon will be used. Off = The curve will be extended to infinity away from the player.
entities.PortalRenderHelper/PortalRenderPoly.attributes.description.flag=Optional flag that can enable / disable the poly. Poly is always active if left blank.
entities.PortalRenderHelper/PortalRenderPoly.attributes.description.invert=Invert how the flag is used. Off = Flag must be enabled for the poly to be enabled, On = Flag must be disabled for the poly to be enabled.
entities.PortalRenderHelper/PortalRenderPoly.attributes.description.portalDepth=Controls the order that portal polygons get rendered. Lower values get rendered first, then higher values overlay the lower ones.
entities.PortalRenderHelper/PortalRenderPoly.attributes.description.angle=The angle in degrees going out relative to the angle going in, where positive is clockwise.


triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.placements.name.default=Set Camera Angle
triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.placements.description.default=Sets the angle and/or the target angle of the camera, as changed by going through rotated portals.

triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.attributes.description.flag=Optional flag that can enable / disable the trigger. Trigger is always active if left blank.
triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.attributes.description.invert=Invert how the flag is used. Off = Flag must be enabled for the trigger to be enabled, On = Flag must be disabled for the trigger to be enabled.
triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.attributes.description.angle=The angle in degrees to set the camera to, where positive angles rotate the camera clockwise.
triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.attributes.description.setAngle=Whether the trigger should set the actual current angle of the camera.
triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.attributes.description.setTargetAngle=Whether the trigger should set the target angle that the camera eases to.
triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.attributes.description.setOnEnter=Whether the trigger activates when the player enters the trigger.
triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.attributes.description.setOnExit=Whether the trigger activates when the player leaves the trigger.
triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.attributes.description.setOnStay=Whether the trigger activates every tick that the player is inside the trigger.
triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.attributes.description.setOnLoad=Whether the trigger activates when the room is entered.
triggers.PortalRenderHelper/SetCameraAngleTrigger.attributes.description.setOnUnload=Whether the trigger activates when the room is left.


